<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-2851] Remove strange public Peek() from Go transports</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-2851</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve been seeing this public Peek() function in the GO library for a while, but&lt;br/&gt;
still cannot figure out any sense to it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If there are useless, we can remove them right?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This PR removes the public Peek() from the implemented transports.&lt;br/&gt;
All tests still pass.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;PR: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/283&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/thrift/pull/283&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
